launch.name: CRS-22 & IROSA
launch.details: SpaceX's 22nd ISS resupply mission on behalf of NASA, this mission sends essential supplies to the International Space Station using the cargo variant of SpaceX's Dragon 2 spacecraft. The external payload for this mission is the first pair of ISS Roll Out Solar Arrays. Falcon 9 and Dragon launch from LC-39A, Kennedy Space Center and the booster is expected to land on an ASDS. The mission will be complete with splashdown and recovery of the capsule and down cargo.
